    local: { show: true, headline: 'Around Madison This Month', text: 'The <strong>Dane County Farmers\' Market</strong> moves back outdoors to the Capitol Square in April \u2014 but March is the month to start planning your garden. Seed starting season is here. Also, keep an eye on the Arboretum trails as the spring thaw reveals some beautiful early wildflowers.' },
    review: { text: 'Great company to work with! They\'re always on time, do excellent work, and are easy to communicate with. Highly recommend TotalGuard to anyone in the Madison area.', name: 'Max Rucker' },
    textBody: 'Hi {{first_name}},\n\nMarch in Madison \u2014 your yard is waking up. Here\'s what to know:\n\n1. Wait to rake until the ground is firm and not saturated.\n2. First mow when grass reaches 3.5-4 inches \u2014 set mower to 3 inches.\n3. Pre-emergent herbicide before soil hits 55\u00b0F consistently.\n\nSpring Package: Cleanup + Mowing + Fertilization \u2014 bundle and save!\n\n"Great company to work with! Always on time, excellent work." \u2014 Max Rucker\n\nBook at tgyardcare.com or call (608) 535-6057'
